On Wed, 2009-05-13 at 11&#58;58, Open Science Grid FootPrints wrote&#58;
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; [Duplicate message snipped]</font></pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='6364#1242230292'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2009-05-13T15:58:12+00:00">May 13, 2009 03:58 PM UTC</time> by <b>Arvind Gopu</b><a class="anchor" name="1242230292">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>(CC&#39;ing ticket <a href='https&#58;//oim.grid.iu.edu/gocticket/viewer?id=6364' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>https&#58;//oim.grid.iu.edu/gocticket/viewer?id=6364</a> that has
been tracking the OIM parts of BNL&#39;s transition)

Hi Xin,

As Brian mentioned I was out on vacation, and got back today. In the
future, if you are in doubt or need immediate attention, feel free to
include goc@.... and/or file a GOC ticket.

<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Arvind -- regarding registering the virtual sitename to OIM without</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; publishing it to WLCG, in order to make the email forward work quickly,</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; do you foresee any problem? Should we go ahead and test it out?</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; It will be like a &#34;virtual&#34; site there. So our questions here are &#58; 1)</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; will the same CEname co-existing in both OIM and WLCG GOCDB cause any</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; problem? Can WLCG BDII incorporate the information from two sources</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; under the same CE name? 2) If we register the BNL-LCG2 name to OIM but</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; not enable the WLCG interoperability function for it, will this make the</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; ticket system WLCG-&#62;OSG-&#62;BNL work, while keeping the OSG BNL-LCG2</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; invisible to WLCG?</font>

1) I think registering resources in both OIM and EGEE&#39;s GOCDB will cause
confusion, as you are aware off. So in the long term, ideally you would
only be registered on OIM.

2) The WLCG interoperability settings should not influence an incoming
GGUS ticket since they just add a resource name, and we (on our end)
just add a CC to the admin&#39;s email address. We should test this just to
be sure when you make such a change.

If I understand the whole thread correctly, OIMv1 (and most definitely
OIMv2 which we expect to release within a week or two) already provide a
way to register FTS and LFCs. And that Xin needs to implement simple
wrappers (GIP providers) to upload information to our GOC BDII, plus add
some configuration to his dCache installation. Please correct me if I am
<div id='show_476238849' class=''><button class="btn">Show More</button></div><div class='detail hidden' id='detail_476238849'>wrong.

Cheers,-ag
