<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; Please read careful about my proposal.  I am asking the feedback</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; about Alessandro&#39;s proposal from various  experts.  I do not</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; understand why you think that i am not reasonable.  Please keep your</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; feedback in a more technical level.   If you have other concern,</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; you, Fred, Rob,  and I can have a meeting to resolve this.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; Please read Alessandro response about adding dcsrm.usatlas.bnl.gov</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; back to BNL-LCG2.  This only involves that BNL site admin goes to the</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; OIM to register a new site name BNL-LCG2.   I am requesting your</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; feedback to this solution.</font>

Repeating what I said before&#58; Xin can make any admin-level changes in
OIM. In case he&#39;s unable to make a change (because of a lacking feature
in OIM or because the change needs GOC authorization), then we&#39;ll be
happy to make the change on his behalf.

Cheers,
Arvind</pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='6364#1234973171'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2009-02-18T16:06:11+00:00">Feb 18, 2009 04:06 PM UTC</time> by <b>dtyu@....</b><a class="anchor" name="1234973171">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Dear All,
