<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; On 2/11/2009 6&#58;12 AM, Alessandro Di Girolamo pondered&#58;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; Ciao *,</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; thanks for all your investigations.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; I&#39;ll try to give my point of view&#58;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; ATLAS uses WLCG resources&#58; that are provided by a mix of egee,</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; osg and nordugrid sites.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; To give realistic, useful, and comparable availability numbers</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; for all the ATLAS sites, and in particular its Tier1, we are</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; using SAM specific VO=ATLAS tests.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; In particular for&#58; SRMv2, CE, LFC and FTS. Those services are</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; needed by ATLAS.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; I think that what should be interesting is the site availability</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; for what concern ATLAS operations, thus we need to have those</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; sites grouped all together into global services, like it is now</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; when we see all the results for SRMv2, CE, FTS and so on.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; let&#39;s take couple of ex.&#58;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; LFC (actually now called LFC_L local)&#58; if in SAM you select this</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; service, you will be able to see all the LFC that are supporting</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; ATLAS (also the lfc.usatlas.bnl.gov). This is ok. Please note</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; that the BNL LFC is below BNL-LCG2 sitename, that is &#34;correctly&#34;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; the BNL tier1 (below the ROC_CERN, but this is another story)</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; SRMv2&#58; we can see all the egee and nordugrid sites, but not the</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; osg ones. If for Tier2s this could be not a problem (I mean not</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; now, less priority), it is a problem for the BNL tier1, since we</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; cannot publish the tests results correctly into GridView. Right</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; now those SRMv2 results are correctly launched, are correctly</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; working, but they are reported below the BNL_ATLAS_SE sitename.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; This sitename is &#34;nothing&#34;, thus gridview cannot understand what</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; site it is, since it&#39;s not attached to any site in the gocdb.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; To be pragmatic, before going too much into &#34;political&#34; issues&#58;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; I see that in</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; <a href='http&#58;//oim.grid.iu.edu/publisher/get_osg_interop_monitoring_list.php' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>http&#58;//oim.grid.iu.edu/publisher/get_osg_interop_monitoring_list.php</a></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; the endpoint dcsrm.usatlas.bnl.gov is only declared in&#58;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; BNL_ATLAS_SE, dcsrm.usatlas.bnl.gov, OSG-SRMv2</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; Why not adding another line like&#58;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; BNL-LCG, dcsrm.usatlas.bnl.gov, SRMv2</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; thus changing the name and the servicetype?</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; in this way in the file we would have ...</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; BNL_ATLAS_SE, dcsrm.usatlas.bnl.gov, OSG-SRMv2</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; BNL-LCG, dcsrm.usatlas.bnl.gov, SRMv2</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; ....</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; I think that SAM could read the last column and see that the</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; dcsrm.usatlas.bnl.gov is both an osg-srmv2 and a &#34;normal&#34; srmv2,</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; thus could put the correct sitename into the osg-srmv2 sites and</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62;&#62; into the srmv2 sites.</font>
