<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62; Dantong Yu wrote&#58;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; Dear All,</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; Sorry to answer late.  I looked over the thread.  I like</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; Alessandro&#39;s proposal to use BNL-LCG2 as site name for merging the</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; LFC, FTS, SRMV2 ATLAS VO test results.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; Last year, I used OSG Information Management system to register</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; dcsrm.usatlas.bnl.gov under site name BNL_ATLAS_SE.   The</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; information was propagated into the WLCG Interoperability BDII.  It</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; was picked up by FTS.  But FTS channels for BNL were all configured</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; to use BNL_LCG2 as end point, and could not recogize BNL_ATLAS_SE.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; All transfers to BNL failed.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; I just want to double check that if we register dcsrm again under</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; BNL_LCG2 and choose the right check box (WLCG Interoperability</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; Monitoring Published to Service Availability Monitoring),  it does</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; not affect FTS operation regarding BNL data transfer.   (I know that</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; dcsrm.usatlas.bnl.gov was already registered under BNL_ATLAS_SE, did</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; not cause any grief to FTS)</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; Here is our plan&#58;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; 1) We will register  dcsrm.usatlas.bnl.gov under BNL_LCG2 via</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; <a href='https&#58;//oim.grid.iu.edu/resource/resource.php.' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>https&#58;//oim.grid.iu.edu/resource/resource.php.</a></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; 2) We will disable the OSG related RSV tests since the same dcache</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; end point was tested already via BNL_ATLAS_SE.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; 3) Alessandro will double check whether such a registration</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; satisfied the Gridview requirement.  So far, there is nothing under</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; BNL_LCG2 in Gridview for ATLAS VO tests.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; As a long term goal,  we should really use a consistent name across</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; EGEE and OSG.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; Thank you very much,</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; Dantong</font>
