Dantong,

Please be reasonable&#58;

1) Your response was at 5 PM yesterday, and it was several days after we
had discussed this issue, and also several days after I had opened a
ticket to track this issue
[I&#39;ve cc&#39;ed the ticket system so the continuation of this
conversation will be easier to track -- ticket
<a href='https&#58;//oim.grid.iu.edu/gocticket/viewer?id=6364' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>https&#58;//oim.grid.iu.edu/gocticket/viewer?id=6364</a> ]
2) There have indeed been several suggestions in this thread as well as
the ticket ... perhaps you didn&#39;t receive those emails?
3) And your response yesterday was partially contradicting what you had
asked for previously in this thread.

Repeating one more time for your benefit, here&#39;s our take on this&#58;

- This is completely ATLAS&#39; call.
- Neither the GOC nor the SAM team has any real say on what you do.
- You should choose what you think is required for ATLAS.
- We have provided every bit of information ATLAS needs to make this
educated decision ...
(refer to this thread and ticket )

Summarizing GOC/RSV/SAM teams take on this&#58; ATLAS would benefit from
<div id='show_468332196' class=''><button class="btn">Show More</button></div><div class='detail hidden' id='detail_468332196'>changing their SE name to BNL_LCG2, and map additional services in OIM.
[this change would require some additional changes in the EGEE side that
James elucidated in the ticket]

PS&#58; GOC would be happy to send a global notification to the community
when the change is made

<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Since the long term solution and associate site name change will pose</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; major impact to the FTS operation and require that all Tier 0/Tier 1</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; site FTS servers to reconfigure their channels to BNL,   I would like</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; to do it after March when ATLAS will  do large scale productions.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; Even we do not expect any potential impact to the OSG/WLCG Grid</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; operation and monitoring, but anyway we would like to send out a</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; global announcement since it might potential affect OSG/WLCG</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; availability number publish and operations which are not directly</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; under BNL site control.</font>
