<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; - Ale, the URL</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; <a href='http&#58;//oim.grid.iu.edu/publisher/get_osg_interop_monitoring_list.php' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>http&#58;//oim.grid.iu.edu/publisher/get_osg_interop_monitoring_list.php</a></font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; is machine generated .. so we cannot add lines to it except when an</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; admin makes a change in their resource registration</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; - Even though there appear to be varying involvement of ATLAS VO,</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; GOC, SAM, etc. the issue is very simple ... BNL (and in this case</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; Dantong/Xin) need to decide if they want synchronized resource names</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; (either BNL_ATLAS_SE or BNL-LCG2) for their SRM, and their CE (as</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; James pointed out) to facilitate RSV based testing as well as VO</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; level tests. Nothing more nothing less, and I am not sure we (RSV or</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; SAM team) can contribute too much more to the case. I suggest</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62; Xin/Dantong and Ale work this out.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;&#62;&#62;</font>
