        </script></pre></div><div class='update_description'><i onclick="document.location='6364#1234535231'; reset_anchor();" class="pull-right icon icon-share"></i><div class="header"><time datetime="2009-02-13T14:27:11+00:00">Feb 13, 2009 02:27 PM UTC</time> by <b>james.casey@....</b><a class="anchor" name="1234535231">&nbsp;</a></div><pre>Hi,

I just want to point out that &#39;Resource group&#39; in OIM and the sitename in BDII needs to be the same.  This was the initial problem for Alessandro  - since the resource group is BNL_ATLAS_SE, SAM sees it in that site, but in the BDII it&#39;s in a different site.

Also, all resources at a site should be in the same resource group, since that&#39;s how we group it for availability calculation - right now we calculate separate availability for BNL_ATLAS_1, BNL_ATLAS_SE and BNL-LCG2 with different services in all of them.

So I see that a single name needs to be chosen for SE, CE, FTS, LFC and all the services put into an appropriate resource group in OIM.

Of course, if the name is not BNL-LCG2 then we&#39;re going to have to change the FTS channel definitions at all sites to
Use the new site name, which will need to be carefully coordinated in order to not cause problems.

Cheers,

James.
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; -----Original Message-----</font>
