<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; problem that BNL meets both ATLAS VO tests and OSG availability tests.  We</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; have to develop a solution to solve it because ATLAS VO tests depends on many</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; LCG specific infrastructure and packages (LFC and FTS) which most OSG sites do</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; not use them.</font>

I am creating this ticket to summarize discussion, GOC, SAM and GridView teams have
had about BNL resources registered on both OIM and GOC DB.

Xin &amp; Dantong, we&#39;d like to recommend that you move all of your BNL resource-service
registrations to OIM. If OIM does not have some detail you&#39;re looking for, then let
us know, and we&#39;ll look into adding that. But I believe it provides everything you
need (including VO-specific services - FTS and LFC).

James, et al - please speak up if I mis-spoke.

Cheers,
Arvind</pre></div><legend>Similar Recent Tickets <small>modified within the last 30 days</small></legend><div id="similar_tickets"><p class="muted">No similar tickets found.</p></div>
